 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-036 FINDING 1: ROADMAP FALSIFICATION. The SEED.md 5-stage roadmap (Stage 0-4) has been falsified by the actual project trajectory. The stages assumed linear progression: CLI → multi-agent. The actual trajectory was: CLI → formal epistemology → self-calibrating attention mechanism. Evidence: (1) Stage 1 defined 'budget-aware output' but the project discovered learned attention (ADR-024), making static budgets a subset. (2) Stage 2 defined 'branching + deliberation' but deliberation was implemented as part of Phase C intelligence, not as a separate stage. (3) Stage 3 defined 'multi-agent coordination' but topology (3K LOC, 75 tests) was built and has never been used with real agents. (4) Stage 4 defined 'advanced intelligence' but the hypothesis ledger, comonadic depth, and attention mechanism emerged from dog-fooding, not from the stage plan. The 5-phase model (Substrate/Lifecycle/Intelligence/Self-Calibration/Active Runtime) better describes both what was built and what remains. VERIFICATION: Compare deliverables per stage vs deliverables per phase. Every completed artifact maps to a phase; many stage boundaries are crossed or irrelevant. IMPACT: Misaligned roadmap causes task inflation (tasks created for stage milestones that don't match actual work), misleading progress percentages (Stage 1 '85%' by original definition, 30% by current understanding), and wasted planning effort."
